  "notes": "Proto-Mon-Khmer (~4000–3000 BCE). Reconstructed ancestor of Mon, Khmer, Vietnamese, Khasi, Nicobarese, Aslian, Bahnaric. Austroasiatic > Mon-Khmer (the non-Munda AA branch). Sesquisyllabic *Cə.CVC; register/phonation contrast; rich vowels with length; palatal stops *c/*ɟ; no proto-tones. Refs: Shorto (2006), Diffloth (2005).",
